    {
      "action": "journal-upsert",
      "id": "v39-cohort",
      "strategy_id": "v39-cohort",
      "cohort_label": "v39",
      "hypothesis": "v39 cohort - entry-gate sweep on the bot-excl-climbing universe. All 5 mirrors share v25-bot-excl-climbing params (filters: top5<=30 + dd>-25 + vel<200 + age>=60 + climbing_t30_t45=1; TP=100/SL=30/entry@T+60/5s poll/no trailing TP). Only entryGateMinPctT30 + entryGateMaxPctT30 vary. Outlier analysis of v25 showed 4 of 7 top losers had entry_pct_from_open > +35% (high-entry fast-rugs at SL in <60s), and big winners spanned the full entry range (+6% to +90%). The climbing_t30_t45 filter passes some dip-recoveries (price down at T+30 but rallying T+45) that the current min=+5 gate excludes - those may be the highest-asymmetry trades. Variants: (5,50) caps upper only; (-25,100) and (-50,100) extend lower; (-25,50) and (-50,50) combine. Goal: identify whether the v25 entry window can be reshaped to cut fast-SL losers without losing the right tail.",
      "prediction": {
        "target_net_sol": 0,
        "target_n": 100,
        "target_days": 21,
        "kill_criterion": "cohort-level - see individual variants"
      },
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
    {
      "action": "journal-upsert",
      "id": "v39-entry-5-50",
      "strategy_id": "v39-entry-5-50",
      "cohort_label": "v39",
      "hypothesis": "Upper-cap only test. Hypothesis: trimming entries with pct_t30 > +50% removes the late-entry fast-rug population (grad 23115 entered at +70% and died in 16s; grad 23889 entered at +63% and died in 109s) without sacrificing most v25 winners (only 1 of 7 top winners entered >+50%, namely grad 23060 at +89.98%). Expected: lower trade volume (~50% of v25), higher per-trade mean, lower SL rate. If trim_mean rises above v25's +0.74% with drop_top3 still positive, the cap is value-additive.",
      "prediction": {
        "target_net_sol": 1.5,
        "target_sol_per_mo": 8,
        "target_drop_top3": 0.3,
        "target_n": 100,
        "target_days": 21,
        "kill_criterion": "n>=60 and net_sol<-1"
      },
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
    {
      "action": "journal-upsert",
      "id": "v39-entry-n25-100",
      "strategy_id": "v39-entry-n25-100",
      "cohort_label": "v39",
      "hypothesis": "Allow modest dippers. Hypothesis: tokens that dipped to -25% by T+30 but are climbing by T+45 are dip-recovery plays - high asymmetric upside (lots of upside room) if the recovery sticks. The current v25 min=+5 hard-excludes these. Trade-off: dippers that DON'T fully recover hit SL fast. If climbing_t30_t45 is a strong-enough recovery signal, the asymmetric payoff should net positive. Expected volume: 110-130% of v25 (adds a population).",
      "prediction": {
        "target_net_sol": 3,
        "target_sol_per_mo": 10,
        "target_drop_top3": 0.8,
        "target_n": 150,
        "target_days": 21,
        "kill_criterion": "n>=75 and net_sol<-1.5"
      },
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
    {
      "action": "journal-upsert",
      "id": "v39-entry-n50-100",
      "strategy_id": "v39-entry-n50-100",
      "cohort_label": "v39",
      "hypothesis": "Aggressive dip-buyer. Hypothesis: -50% at T+30 with confirmed climb at T+45 is a 'caught knife' - either a true recovery (big upside, room to run multi-x) or a dead-cat bounce. Memecoin distribution should give a small percentage of these true recoveries that pay 200%+, offsetting the SL fires. Higher-variance bet vs (-25,100). If drop_top3 stays positive this is the highest-EV variant. If drop_top3 is negative, this is pure lottery-ticket noise.",
      "prediction": {
        "target_net_sol": 3,
        "target_sol_per_mo": 10,
        "target_drop_top3": 0.5,
        "target_n": 150,
        "target_days": 21,
        "kill_criterion": "n>=75 and net_sol<-1.5"
      },
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
    {
      "action": "journal-upsert",
      "id": "v39-entry-n25-50",
      "strategy_id": "v39-entry-n25-50",
      "cohort_label": "v39",
      "hypothesis": "Tightened both sides. Hypothesis: pct_t30 in [-25, +50] is the 'sweet spot' band - excludes both the late-momentum-chasers (>+50 entries) and the deep-dippers (<-25). Should produce the highest per-trade mean and the cleanest distribution shape. Cost: lowest trade volume of the 5 variants. If this wins on trim_mean + drop_top3 but loses on total_net_sol, the band is right but coverage is too narrow.",
      "prediction": {
        "target_net_sol": 1.5,
        "target_sol_per_mo": 6,
        "target_drop_top3": 0.3,
        "target_n": 80,
        "target_days": 21,
        "kill_criterion": "n>=50 and net_sol<-1"
      },
      "status": "OPEN"
    },
    {
      "action": "journal-upsert",
      "id": "v39-entry-n50-50",
      "strategy_id": "v39-entry-n50-50",
      "cohort_label": "v39",
      "hypothesis": "Wide-lower + capped-upper combo. Hypothesis: combine the asymmetric-upside of dip-recoveries (lower bound -50) with the fast-SL protection of capping high entries (upper bound 50). If both effects compound, this is the best variant. If they cancel (dippers add SL count faster than the cap saves), result will be neutral. Volume should be ~80-100% of v25 (gains dippers, loses high-entries).",
      "prediction": {
        "target_net_sol": 3,
        "target_sol_per_mo": 10,
